Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharp turn. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine light brown; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.101a, 61). Name Marsyas.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0799)
